references:
We prepare 145 features for modeling semantic similarity (Table¬†3). Edit distance is the Levenshtein distance between strings, length is measured in characters, and maximum or minimum is
between all word pairs in the corresponding context regions. Since we have 3x3 regions in inter-cwps, together with their row and column averages, we obtain 16 features. We also obtain the wps values
after mean / min / max of the regional mean / min / max values since a single word can affect the semantics of the whole region or context.
